caption: Incredible food and extremely friendly service! The interior of the restaurant is beautiful bordering on intimate, and the cuisine sets a very high bar for both Laotian food and southeast asian food in the District.

Incredibly delicious. The food is exquisite and the service is great. You can tell they are very proud of what they do here. I got the chicken curry yesterday and i was thinking about eating the leftovers all day today lol. Their beef soup with bean sprouts is also very delicious. I cannot wait to go again with friends and try out their appetizers and drinks.
This place here is one of the best spot in dc if you want to experience something different. The food is amazing i love it..if u go tell them i scent you

Never tries Laos foods before and a friend recommended me to check this place cause I'm a sucker for Thai food. I'm so happy he did it! I had the best time and the dishes still gives my craves whenever I think about them

My boyfriend and I went for Valentine’s Day and it was incredible. The entrees are well priced, perfectly proportioned, and delicious. They also have really interesting drinks (although a bit pricey). The dessert menu was also good, but we opted for one of the specialty cakes they have delivered every Friday— each flavor is only available for that week. The almond chocolate slice we had was really good.

Very good Lao food. If you haven’t had it, some dishes are very similar to Thai. The orm soup with sticky rice is oh-so-good, and you can’t go wrong with any of the curries. I also loved both the vegan mango salad and the crispy rice salad (which can be served vegan or with crispy pork). Very reasonable prices too. Will be returning for sure.

Laos tofu. Service is excellent all the time. Our most recent server was Abbie I’ve been at this restaurant so many times and I always forget to leave a review honestly the only dish I get is the Laos tofu and it is so delicious every time definitely come and experience at least one of the dishes at this place the vegetarian rolls an excellent

Exceptional food - worth every penny! The rockfish is incredible, mango salad is delightful and the chicken curry is always wonderful! They are not afraid of spice and the flavor is bold. Also when delivered it is always hot and well packaged. Highly recommend!
Love this spot. The minced pork (lab moo) and sour pork sausage fried rice are my fav!

My brother from NYC and I were enjoying the service and food from this restaurant. Everything was great, left a nice tip and all. Until that night. I lost half the night of sleep with digestive problems and vomiting the next day.  Please avoid their most expensive fish dish. As that was my main meal and I gave my brother a sample of it. He also had digestive problems but much shorter duration than mine.  Since it was my first time there I will assume all of the other dishes were just as great as reviewed. I hate to set such a bad review because everything else was on point but I was out of commission for a day after eating here.

Love this place!  Best Lao food in D.C! Loved the variety on the menu and found the flavors to be on point! Definitely get the sin heng (beef jerky) and the the grilled fish! The tamarind sauce is delish! I also got the papaya salad and quail and was very delighted! Great service as well. We dined outside and felt very safe! Also. You MUST get the Lao coffee! It’s so smooth and yummy!

We just order some food from here, papaya was ok, sticky was TRASH, super HARD it's like they gave us old sticky rice 🙄🤦‍♀️, fried rice was ok, we also order "rock fish" i believe that's what its called for $30...was it worth the price? Most definitely not, however super convenient, more on the sweet side, super crunchy over all it was ok, but will I buy it again? Definitely not for $30!!! Spent over $70 for all this 🤦‍♀️🙄 the ONLY thing we got that i felt was authentic was the papaya only.

Laos In Town came as a recommendation from a friend, and he was spot on! The Herbal Sausage was spicy, flavorful and the dipping sauce was a perfect compliment.  I love spicy papaya salads and the Meakong Salad delivered a nice kick.  For dessert I had the Khao Niao Mak Muang), which is your standard mango sticky rice.  The portions are enough for sharing or leftovers.  I haven't had the pleasure of dining at the restaurant, but hope to once the weather and COVID restrictions permit.  In the meantime, takeout is a great option to enjoy their great food!
Consistently delicious, any day of the week. A mainstay in the neighborhood.
Outdoor seating, cocktails, and service were good. But the food was flavorless *and* overcooked. We have not been this disappointed by an Asian restaurant for a very long time.
Delicious Laotian food. Lots of vegan options. Outdoor dog friendly seating with heaters for winter
Fantastic food, much better than many places nearby. Highly recommend!
The food was great! Very flavorful and fresh. Definitely gonna come back.
Amazing food! I am so glad I tried this place, everything we ordered was extremely delicious, but their Wok was something else 🤎🤎

Top 10 meals this year, you have to try the quail. Super flavorful, perfect spice levels and unique offerings. The pictures don’t do justice as we got everything to go. The bar area looks amazing with tons of outdoor seating, we will certainly be stopping by again when we’re in town.

Love it! The food was awesome and the service as well. I love calamari and this place is the second place I've visited where the calamari is prepped and cooked  perfectly. The decor of the place is pretty nice as well!
(Translated by Google) Uuuf the taste of everything delicious. Very nice place inside and outside  (Original) Uuuf el sabor de todo riquísimo. Local muy lindo dentro y fuera

username: m i c h a e l

caption: Great food, friendly staff wonderful decor.
Very good Laotian restaurant in DC!
Beautiful restaurant with fantastic food. I cant wait to try more items off the menu

I have been here multiple times and always try to order different things on the menu and each time I am blown away by how amazing the food is. Can't explain how much I love this place. This is our go-to place when we have friends come to town to visit!
So good! Drinks too.
Decent food, but extremely overpriced. I have eaten at better restaurants for 3x less.
While not inexpensive, the food was very good and very authentic. Sitting on their patio felt like sitting at a street cafe in Vientiane. Minus the loud motor scooters, of course.
Delicious food in a very nice patio setting.

The mango salad is really fresh; the fried tofu, cashews, and onion contrast nicely with the sweetness of the mango. Highly recommend the Northern noodle, which has pickled radishes that cut the heat, and the lemongrass fizz, a mocktail with lychee juice that isn’t too sweet. Everything I’ve had from here is delicious. Pro tip: use their own website for delivery so the delivery apps don’t take a cut. They’re just as quick, and you can order a super cute $5 mask through their website, too.

Really liked my food. I also enjoyed the outdoor seating and it was such a nice place for a Sunday night dinner with friends! Only reason I gave 4 stars is there were some dishes that my friends weren’t big fans of. I really liked my curry noodle chicken.
Generally very excellent, but recently we ordered Northern Noodle to go and this dish is supposed to come with 2 legs, but it only had 1 leg in there. $15 for a leg, some curry, and noodles

TAKE BETTER PRECAUTIONS for COVID-19. The hostess didn’t wear her mask properly - her nose was out. It was alarming. They handed out two menus - one of which was definitely reused among people. Our table had 4 servers who didn’t provide space and who were running around asking the same questions. Limit exposure, servers. We were the first to arrive and even though it was outside, the place got packed.  The food is okay - they messed up my order (probably bc they were running around all the tables). DC should not encourage restaurant week (I didn’t know it was) to reduce crowding.  Is there some type of checklist restaurants need to go through with their employees to reopen? They definitely didn’t go through any steps.
This place is a gem! Love their stews. Orm was my favorite. Some of dishes can be very spicy. They also offer vegetarian menu, which was great.
Excellent food. Really appreciated that they have a vegan menu
Very tasty.
Amazing experience in the world of unforgettable taste!

Laos in Town has become a go-to restaurant for an amazing meal. Not a month goes by without ordering a dinner from here. I'm a big fan of the Poh Pia starter, a crispy vegetable spring roll with sweet and sour sauce. I like to pair this with the Wok Noodle, a delectable rice noodle with bean sprouts and sauce.
Everything was sour. Every single dish. No complexity in the flavor profile. Will not order again. I would leave two stars but my better half said I shouldn’t do that during COVID-19 times.
The coconut custard and sticky rice is AMAZING. The outdoor seating and bar are very welcoming with the right amount of attention to detail and service.

Thank you for an amazing dinner.  I love eating in but the take out was amazing! First time for my husband but the look on his face says big win for Laos in town. Flavor coma! Couldn’t be happier. Stay safe!
Really great takeout, a perfect way to break the monotony with selfish and exciting food.
Highly recommend the orm stew and the mieng kana! They  have a fantastic menu with a variety of unique and authentic dishes. I can't wait to go back and try more!
We really loved the orm, but all we tried was tasty!
Awesome little spot with authentic food and quality service. Will return!

VEGAN ONLY MENU REVIEW : Such a bummer experience. My date and I ordered 4 items off the vegan menu: The Poh Pia spring rolls were tasty (served with a sweet & sour type sauce) however was a bit confused as the menu description highly suggested we wrap the rolls in lettuce before dipping/eating. Six small rolls + 3 small pieces of lettuce = 3 stragglers without a blanket. The other appetizer we ordered, Bai Mun (flat fried potato leaves) roughly the equivalent of a kale chip but thinner/more airy. At a $6.00 price point we were shocked to see maybe six leaves on the plate. Either serve 4x that amount or take it off the menu. I honestly sat and looked at the plate for a few seconds thinking that it was a mistake.  We were pretty hungry so we each got one of the two main tofu dishes, he got the flat noodles and I got the fried rice. My portions were very big, while his was much smaller. The noodles were okay and the tofu in each dish was good, but the rice was flavorless and also a tad bitter with the scallions/unseasoned broccoli/cabbage. To power through the dish I ended up using all the remaining appetizer sauces and sriracha to help the rice along. It was a TON of rice, just not in a good way. :(  Server was friendly but didn't really listen when I tried to respond to his "how is everything?" question. I started to ask him about the leafy appetizer and he said "okay great!" and walked away. So odd. We skipped dessert because we were already let down and didn't feel like adding to the bill. Honestly we were very excited to eat here, but we won't be back. Sad times.

Great Laotian place! There are a variety of options, but everything was delicious. The tofu dishes especially were a standout, both the fried rice and the rolls we got as a starter. Good happy hour deals as well, if you come on the earlier side.

Wonderfully innovative combinations of flavours. We had the fried quail, chicken heart (yum!), chef's signature papaya salad and deep fried whole rockfish (amazing!). Topped off with the mango sticky rice which again combined sweet, salty and umami in an interesting and delicious way. Wait staff were all very friendly and helpful. Note: if you're not too good with spicy food, be sure to order the Thai iced tea.
Food was good and service was friendly

Tried out during Restaurant Week and will definitely be back. Worth the trip to the area for. Food was good and they were able to accommodate some dietary restrictions, such as gluten free and pescatarian. I, as many other diners, initially wanted to compare with Thip Khao in Columbia Heights. Both are good and, while the same cultural cuisine, are distinct restaurants that are both great.  A couple areas for improvement- we were seated right next to the service area and it was of course very chaotic. The server also initially charged us full price for drinks and it took several employees before anyone believed us (and the menu) that it was happy hour drink prices
Very quick service, friendly staff, the food was delicious.
The food was very good.  I ordered the grilled chicken and chicken lettuce wraps. Attentive service.  They were out of the mango sticky rice but that was minor

If you like Thai food, Laotian food might not be much of a stranger. You will find similarity in the ingredient, the seasoning, and the flavors. I never had Laotian food before Laos in Town, so I looked forward to it. I wanted to experience the food without the hefty airlines ticket and 24 hour flight.  We were seated promptly upon arriving with a reservation. Apparently there was a vegetarian menu, but since we were omnivores, we skipped on that.  Kate took care of us really well and made some very good recommendations on drinks and food: I had the fighting tiger and top notch. They put up a fight and were both top notch.  Food-wise, I loved the strong flavors and aromas of the dishes we ordered. I'd recommend these 3 dishes if you want something exotic and special to this restaurant: - Herbal pork sausage: tasty with lemongrass and peppercorn - Seen hang: Laotian beef jerky. A good snack food. - Crispy rice salad: strong in flavor but balanced with the freshness of the salad, and crunchy in texture.  Although the other dishes are on the menu at other Thai or Asian restaurants, these are good in their own rights at Laos in Town: - Calamalao : big rings of squids fried with slight batter. - Grilled beef: tender and seasoned the Asian way. - Khua mee: pad thai served in a small wok  Overall, I am glad I was able to experience something old and new, strange and familiar.

This is Asian food made for white people, and it’s DELICIOUS. If you’ve ever been unsure about Asian inspired food, you’ll definitely find something here you’ll love. If you’re well acquainted with East Asian food and you’re looking for something a little new, you’ll love it here  The atmosphere can feel a little stuffy, but the servers are very incredibly kind and inviting. They outdoor seating is generous.
Great place to grab a drink and eat some dinner. The outdoor space during the warmer months is excellent. Friendly staff that always makes you feel welcomed!
Very good and flavorful food

Excellent service and great food! Will certainly be back to try other offerings on the menu! Went with friends during DC Winter Restaurant Week. The place was overbooked but managed to squeeze us in for a quick meal. Wait staff was courteous and made great recommendations for the group. Appetizers, main courses and desserts were all delicious. Great experience overall!

I came here with three other people during restaurant week. The food was simply fantastic. DC sets a very high bar for Northern Thai/ Lao food, and this is one of the best. Every dish was amazing, the service was good, the place was insanely packed (that's DC for you), but they didn't hurry us out. We really enjoyed it.
Great food and great service. The staff were very friendly and fast. We were here for restaurant week and the food was amazing with great flavors and presentation

This was my first experience with Laotian food and it really good. Super interesting flavors and I like that the front has a lot of cookbooks to peruse while you're waiting for a table.  The first time we went, they did have a problem with getting us seated (even though we had a reservation), but they made it up to us with a free appetizer.

Was really excited to try this place. Amazing decor and food looked/smelled great. Made an advanced reservation a couple days before and ended up waiting an hour after checking in at the restaurant before leaving. Management needs better service.
Unfortunately, this is the most mediocre food I have eaten in DC. The place is good looking but the service felt overwhelmed by the restaurant week crowd and the food lacked flavor.

Their website has a "book a table" option. Fill out the form and you get a message that says "your reservation is set." Show up and they tell you that just put you on a wait list and isn't really a reservation.

Wait staff excellent in both service and suggestions. We had broiled whole fish which was delicious but watch out for the bones. Crispy rice salad excellent. We shared three desserts among five of us and those were great. Not crazy about the lettuce wraps. Decor was sophisticated but not glitzy .
Fantastic and authentic food.  Wait staff was friendly and accommodating. I can't wait to come back again.

Came here with a Laotian friend. We had the crispu fish and fish curry with sticky rice. Great service, beautiful interior and delicious food. If u are a fan of spicey, sour and savory flavors, i recommend.
Outstanding addition to our neighborhood.
Really great food and the service was on point!
Great dinner. Make sure you try the chicken hearts appetizer. Very good service.

One of the best south east aisian curries I've had locally. The atmosphere is a little austere but that's largely outside the restaurant's control. Looking forward to coming with a crew to try everything
The food was excellent the service was wonderful

Cool ambience with a funky modern vibe. Love the mix of texture throughout the restaurant with bamboo, marble, and brick.  Top dishes - Orm soup and  the crispy rice salad. The broth in the Orm soup was incredible. Spicy but not over powering, filled with vegetables and chicken. The crispy rice salad is perfect for texture people, but the citrusy pop from the lemongrass is what won me over.  Must try new restaurant in DC.  See more food pics from me on Instagram @whetyourappetites

This place was really good. I got takeout but it looked nice inside. Got the pork sausage, chicken hearts (a little tough but I think that's the texture of heart), and the spicy catfish. Everything was really good. I know spice tolerance is subjective but I found the spice to be right at a nice threshold. I'm glad to see more Laotian restaurants around.
Very good food. It was a little on the salty side.
Excellent food and service.
Came here after I moved close by & it fast became my regular because of the service. The food is great but Ted’s drinks are hard to beat. Definitely recommend.
Need benches along the sidewalk. Some shade would be nice.
Wonderful authentic food and great service!

I came with my girlfriend to have dinner for the first time, and it certainly won't be the last. So far, this is our favorite restaurant in DC. Great food (like amazing) and very kind staff. Decoration and ambiance is very nice. If you come here please order crispy rice salad (spicy and sour for lemon lovers) the coconut sticky rise desert! You're welcome in advance.
I was a great experience i would also recommend it to my friends and colleagues
Good food, good Wait Staff, I will definitely go again.

What a fantastic experience and delicious food! I enjoyed the 4 times I went there over the 2 days I was in DC. Yes it is that good. Their wings they have at lunch are to die for. DONT GET MAD ABOUT THE SIZE OF THE WINGS, they are small but so worth it because they are packed with flavor and the sauce that comes with them tastes so good. And the Butterfly Lemonade is an amazing drink, get it! The entrees are all great and if you still have space after get their mango sticky rice, what a great sweet! Also big shoutout to Flo who waited on us the first time and always talked to us and was funny and friendly when we would return. 5/5 stars!
Really good thai food. Great service.
Absolutely great food & fun ambience. Fabulous & attentive service.
Don’t order curry, beyond sweet, too much coconut cream. Authentic dishes were decent, but portions are pretty small for the price. Sticky rice was really dry. Very nice service and good seating.
Got the fried rice and it was delicious!
I am half Laotian and this food is legit! Very tasty and very fun place!

Visited here for work yesterday. Never had Laotian food. I ordered crispy quail and crispy chicken wings. If you've never had quail, I def recommend it. I actually enjoyed it better than the chicken, though both were good. Service is pretty quick, but the space is rather small, so it could be tough to get a table when it's busy. Staff are very friendly. Id go back. The fish looked really good. Didn't try it but if I go back soon, I just might.
Really enjoyable meal! The flavors reminded me of eating next to the Mekong river. I'd love to go back and try more of their dishes.
Great
Clean, nice decor, and authentic Laos food.  Their dip of basalt/tamarin fish sauce with whole grilled fish is delicious.
Great food at reasonable prices! The vegan fried rice might be the best I've ever had.
Pretty good cocktails! I have to comeback for their food! Ted definitely took care of us!
Love the bar! Great bartender
Pretty authentic when it comes to Laotian, and just as tasty as thip khao, but more expensive with smaller serving size.

Delicious dishes at a good price.  The service was very fast, despite being packed at lunch time.  Good selection of appetizers (the quail wings were great), soups, noodles, seafood, vegetarian and meat based dishes.

Delightful dining experience in NoMa. Just a few blocks from the NoMa Metro stop, this place really hit the spot. With a MASSIVE outdoor patio and plenty of seating indoors, Laos in Town can accommodate a lot of guests. The interior was clean and attractive. The staff was friendly, the drinks were nice (special shout out to the Thai iced tea). The food was quick and absolutely delicious. Our fav was the khua khao. So damn good.

Took the first suggestion from the gracious host who recommended quickly for me a nice spicey dish. I was encouraged to sit down at the bar and grab a water. I had the dish within 5 minutes.  I was really pleased with the spice amount as should be expected from an ethnic restaurant in cosmopolitan D.C. About two thirds of my to go box was a sticky white rice which initially turned me off but became necessary to  balance the heat from the food. I wish they'd have included a wedge of lime or a picked radish or something to break up the monotony of the dish.  Overall it's a gorgeous restaurant which had a great flavorful entree that I will hopefully have a chance to go back to for a seated occasion and more leasierly exploration of Laotian cuisine.

YUMMMMM!! Very cool decor, attentive staff, limited but interesting and delicious menu of dishes, and supposedly great drinks (I take my friend's work for it). The patio is quite large as well and right across the street from the wonder that is Indigo so there's a cool community feel around here.

Amazing authentic savory, spicy, sour and sweet noodles, soups, meats, fish, tofu, salads and rice based Laotian dishes with authentic and sometimes unfamiliar ingredients.  Numerous Vegetarian and Vegan options, too.

Laos in Town was a great experience and the service was very welcoming. The interior was well decorated and very pleasing on the eye. The food was great as well. Would recommend the crispy chicken wings and papaya salad. The patio space was also very large and would be great on a sunny day.

Fantastic and sophisticated southeast Asian flavors. Many ( most) of the dishes are spicy so watch out but the cocktails are a fantastic salve. The sticky rice is fantastic an even the more familiar cities are made to a standard a step above
This place is fabulous, the food is delicious, I recommend it a lot.
The food here is amazing. The staff is very friendly and helpful. The location is great and the atmosphere is gorgeous. I highly recommend!
Great patio and decent food.
Food was delicious but service was really bad. We end up taking some of our food to go after staying there for 2.5 hours.
Fast and friendly service.

Loved this place! Got 4 appetizers-my favorites were the pork shoulder and egg rolls. But the best part was dessert-sticky rice and custard! Very sweet server, everything brought out in a timely manner, and beautiful decor.
Great flavor and spice.
Better than Thip Khao

This restaurant was alright. The vibes here are great the out door seating and the ambience is fantastic. I wasn't blown away by the good. It was ok. I ordered the Khua Khao chicken see the picture below but it was just like some regular chicken fried rice you can get from any Chinese restaurant. The catfish however was good. My biggest complaint was the Chaophraya salad which doesn't list shrimp any where in the description but it contained shrimp. This is a problem because I'm allergic to shellfish.

Pros: space is beautiful, table server was nice, chicken curry was delish Cons: food runner was oblivious, chicken wings were raw ( yes, even though they were tiny & looked burnt) small portions Was looking forward to the experience and left disappointed and $50 poorer MEH
Spicy delicious foods! Lots of menu options including vegan menu
I wanted a quick bite, so I ordered the grilled pork starter, I have no complaints in regards to the portion, but it was burnt.
Crispy Rockfish was really good! It is casual place but the interior design makes it look super fancy.
Amazing food matched with incredible service.
Fantastic food! Wonderful use of space space! Both indoor and outdoor seating and a great bar area.

Had 4 items off of the vegan menu  Tofu laab-delicious! Sticky crunch rice salad-the ginger was too overpowering but it was interesting Tofu curry-delicious red curry Tofu orm-didn’t like it. Also very spicy.  Mango sticky rice-it was good but nothing special that made it stand out from others  Prices were very reasonable. Service was fabulous. The environment/decor was great too!
Wonderful food and service! Beautiful restaurant

If I had paid a third of the price for the food that I ate today, I wouldn't be so disappointed. My experience started off kind of poorly because the bartender didn't acknowledge me until I finally said "Hey! May I please have a menu and order and drink?" That was after waiting about 8 minutes for her to look at me, although...she knew I was there because I asked if the seat was empty when I arrived. The atmosphere is fantastic. I love that you can sit outside (with a dog) right at the bar. The inside looks beautiful although I remained outdoors. I order 2 apps for there and then a bunch of other items to go. The jumbo prawns were good and the dipping sauce was very nice and spicy. That's where the good stuff ends. I also ordered the chicken lettuce wraps and even though the chicken was flavorful and nice, it was a very tiny amount. I can't imagine trying to share that appetizer with another person. I ordered a pulled chicken soup that was full of mushrooms, a tiny amount of chicken, and A LOT of lemon flavor. For an $8 soup, it was tiny. The menu also said it had a "spicy aftertaste" but that certainly was not the case. I also ordered the Signature salad and will admit, I had no clue it wouldn't be a salad at all. My bad. It looked like a Thai dish with thin sprouts, some sort of pork patty, a fee green beans and what looked like pork rinds (?), It was just meh. The biggest disappointment was the grilled beef main dish. For $18, I got about 10 very thin slices of beef, placed on a banana leaf with a glob of sticky rice on the side. The rough ground chili sauce that it's supposed to be dressed with was barely noticeable and definitely not spicy. The price of this dish is outstanding considering the tiny amount of food. I also ordered dessert of course...mango sticky rice. The mango was served with the peel still attached. Is that a thing?? I've never seen that before and I can't imagine trying to eat that appropriately if dining there. Over all, after an $87 meal, I'm still hungry and really disappointed. Was really looking forward to a new, interesting restaurant to try. I'd go back, but only for drinks, and only if there's a new bartender. Bummer.
I had a wonderful experience at Laos. The food was amazing and arrived quickly, the restaurant was beautiful and my server David was funny and kind.
Wow love this restaurant! Very nice and the Khua mee was yummy

I went here last night with my friends and we were all a bit disappointed with the portion of the food that came out for the price that we had to pay. We ordered 3 different appetizers ($7-$8 each) and all of them were microscopic, every time the server placed down a plate, we all had the same feeling, “That’s it??” The poh pia (eggrolls) were so TINY. The restaurant surely can afford to give each person one WHOLE eggroll instead of cutting up one piece into 4 microscopic pieces for us to fight over, especially for the price that we’re paying. The main entrees then came out. Again, the portion sizes were so, SO small. These entrees are not cheap and for the amount we’re paying, we expected to receive more food. The restaurant is definitely stingy on their ingredients and you’ll constantly be thinking, “Wow, that’s all the food I get for $15? What a rip off.” The menu items are equivalent to typical street food you’d find in Thailand, but here they try to spin it as if they’re fancy dishes and therefore slap a high price tag on it. Papaya salads in Thailand/Laos are equivalent to $1 street tacos that some lady is selling off of a cart, not some luxurious gourmet item whatsoever. Same with the chicken and sticky rice, $13 for one chicken leg quarter and a tiny amount of sticky rice, what the heck? Go to Thailand and that’s like buying a hot dog.  The bathroom looks nice, but there’s no toilet seat cover. What do they do instead? Leave a bottle of sanitizer and paper towels for you to wipe the toilet seat. You get to be both a customer and a custodial worker at the same time.

Loved it. Great service, we had a wonderful waitress who really helped us get through the menu and make good recommendations. The quality of the food was great and decor was beautiful. Definitely stop in!

I was so excited to see this place come into the neighborhood. Finally went for the first time today, and it exceeded my expectations!! The food was incredible, the restaurant itself is beautifully decorated, and the staff was amazing. Our server Lee had great recommendations and was super friendly and fun! Also love that there is an outside bar! Will definitely be coming back!
We were passing by and decided to try it on a whim. The food and drinks were great. We could tell the staff was a little new to the menu, but that didn't impact the meal at all.
